091Sm 28:7 Saul then said to his advisers, "Find a woman who is a medium, so I can go and ask her what to do." His advisers replied, "There is a medium at Endor."
091Sm 28:8 So Saul disguised himself by wearing ordinary clothing instead of his royal robes. Then he went to the woman's home at night, accompanied by two of his men. "I have to talk to a man who has died," he said. "Will you call up his spirit for me?"
091Sm 28:9 "Are you trying to get me killed?" the woman demanded. "You know that Saul has outlawed all the mediums and all who consult the spirits of the dead. Why are you setting a trap for me?"
091Sm 28:10 But Saul took an oath in the name of the LORD and promised, "As surely as the LORD lives, nothing bad will happen to you for doing this."
091Sm 28:11 Finally, the woman said, "Well, whose spirit do you want me to call up?" "Call up Samuel," Saul replied.
091Sm 28:12 When the woman saw Samuel, she screamed, "You've deceived me! You are Saul!"
091Sm 28:13 "Don't be afraid!" the king told her. "What do you see?" "I see a god¨ç coming up out of the earth," she said. / ¨ç{Or gods}
091Sm 28:14 "What does he look like?" Saul asked. "He is an old man wrapped in a robe," she replied. Saul realized it was Samuel, and he fell to the ground before him.
091Sm 28:15 "Why have you disturbed me by calling me back?" Samuel asked Saul. "Because I am in deep trouble," Saul replied. "The Philistines are at war with me, and God has left me and won't reply by prophets or dreams. So I have called for you to tell me what to do."
091Sm 28:16 But Samuel replied, "Why ask me, since the LORD has left you and has become your enemy?
091Sm 28:17 The LORD has done just as he said he would. He has torn the kingdom from you and given it to your rival, David.
