091Sm 28:23 But Saul refused to eat anything. Then his advisers joined the woman in urging him to eat, so he finally yielded and got up from the ground and sat on the couch.
091Sm 28:24 The woman had been fattening a calf, so she hurried out and killed it. She took some flour, kneaded it into dough and baked unleavened bread.
091Sm 28:25 She brought the meal to Saul and his advisers, and they ate it. Then they went out into the night.
091Sm 29:1 The entire Philistine army now mobilized at Aphek, and the Israelites camped at the spring in Jezreel.
