091Sm 29:11 So David and his men headed back into the land of the Philistines, while the Philistine army went on to Jezreel.
091Sm 30:1 Three days later, when David and his men arrived home at their town of Ziklag, they found that the Amalekites had made a raid into the Negev and Ziklag; they had crushed Ziklag and burned it to the ground.
091Sm 30:2 They had carried off the women and children and everyone else but without killing anyone.
091Sm 30:3 When David and his men saw the ruins and realized what had happened to their families,
091Sm 30:4 they wept until they could weep no more.
091Sm 30:5 David's two wives, Ahinoam from Jezreel and Abigail, the widow of Nabal from Carmel, were among those captured.
091Sm 30:6 David was now in great danger because all his men were very bitter about losing their sons and daughters, and they began to talk of stoning him. But David found strength in the LORD his God.
091Sm 30:7 Then he said to Abiathar the priest, "Bring me the ephod!" So Abiathar brought it.
